}

q {
Q:"An A.P., a G.P. and a H.P. have the same first and last terms and the same odd numbers of terms, the middle terms of the three series are in:"
A:"b"
O:a) "A.P.", b) "G.P.", c) "H.P.", d) "None of these"
R:"Let first term \\(a\\), last term \\(b\\). Middle term of A.P is \\((a+b)/2\\). Middle term of G.P is \\(\\sqrt{ab}\\). Middle term of H.P is \\(2ab/(a+b)\\). These three values satisfy the geometric mean relationship: \\(\\sqrt{ab}^2 = \\frac{a+b}{2} \\cdot \\frac{2ab}{a+b}\\). Thus, they are in G.P."
}

